<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="276" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d276">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 657.119/387b</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-01">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 1, 1918</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>7103. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from War Trade Board]:</p>
                            <p>No. 279. Repeat to <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SAG1">Schmedeman</persName>:</p>
                            <p>The following memorandum represents the present status of our
                                negotiations with Doctor <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_NF1">Nansen</persName>. It contains some matters still under
                                discussion but Doctor <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_NF1">Nansen</persName> believes that if it is given to his
                                Government in order that they may cable him their comments time will
                                be saved in reaching a final conclusion.</p>
                            <p>[Here follows text of the draft agreement.<note n="1" xml:id="d276fn1">Generally identical with the final text
                                    printed, <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1170">p.
                                        1170</ref>, except for certain alterations made in
                                    consequence of the Norwegian negotiator’s letter of Apr. 12, <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1155">p.
                                        1155</ref>. Passages of the draft which were radically
                                    altered in the final text are printed as footnotes to the
                                    pertinent portions of that letter.</note>]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>